# BlameLess — environment configuration
#
# A read-only GitHub token. A classic PAT with `public_repo` scope is enough
# (PostHog/posthog is public); a fine-grained token with read access to contents,
# pull requests, and issues also works. No write scopes are needed.
#
# If GITHUB_TOKEN is not set, the scripts fall back to `gh auth token` (the gh CLI
# keyring), so an authenticated `gh` install needs no .env at all.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Optional deploy credentials (only if you choose to automate deploys yourself).
# VERCEL_TOKEN=
# NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=
